== Extracted Lists

 The list environments below are extracted from arXiv LaTeX source and wrapped for pdfLaTeX validation.

/ Fig.1 Plot of the region in parameter space $(a, b)$ allowed by the inflationary conditions in the text. The solid lines represent those bounds which do not depend on the scale $M $ of the phase transition. The dashed curve correspond to the bounds associated with the scale $M = 1 0^(1 1)$ GeV and the dotted curve to those related to $M = 1 0^(1 6)$ GeV. The allowed region is the one below the curves. The border $b = 0 $ is excluded from it. We have labelled the curves as follows: QG corresponds to the condition associated to neglecting quantum gravity effects, $Phi $ corresponds to the condition for an increasing scalar field, RW corresponds to the bound on isotropy and homogeneity at the time of nucleosynthesis and pN--NS corresponds to the bounds from post--Newtonian experiments and the nucleosynthesis bound on $omega $.

